In a democracy the rule is that judicial decisions are public. 
The society that does not know how and why the judges decides, is not a free society. 
In ordinary proceedings, the publicit is guaranteed with publication of judgments in official journals. 
The processes in small claims courts do not have this obligation. 
The decision of the small claims Court of the Court of Justice of Bahia, for example, 
they are not published without the daily newspaper.

This project aims to copy all decisions of small courts in the State of Bahia, indexes them, and publishes them.
